data.description: Beautiful one-level 3 bedroom/2 bathroom mountain home only 10 minutes from Downtown Boone and Appalachian State University. This home is on 1.62 gently sloped acres directly off of maintained paved roads which provide year-round access. This wonderfully landscaped lot sits right inside the Mast Ridge subdivision. It comes furnished and ready for you to move in or rent out. There is a detached one-car garage, a covered entry porch, a large covered deck with layered mountain views, and an easy-care landscaped yard.  The large yard contains raspberries, blueberries, and a pear tree. Recent improvements include a heat pump/AC and water heater updated in 2019, a new well pump and propane furnace in 2020, and repaved driveway in 2021. The house has a well-planned layout including an open-concept living, dining, and kitchen all in the center of the home, and bedrooms on both ends. The large primary ensuite is on one end of the home while two other bedrooms have a full bathroom in between on the other side.  Wood floors in the open area along with granite countertops, solid wood cabinets, and an island in the kitchen make for an excellent gathering place. Large windows along the front give a view from almost everywhere in the house. Relax and sit on the front porch swing and enjoy the view and peace and quiet.  Great central location to major High Country areas... Boone, Valle Crucis, Sugar Grove, and Watauga Lake too. Fiber optic cable was brought in the neighborhood but sellers never connected. The buyer's agent should verify what is available for the internet.  The Sellers have recently tested the well water and the results came back clean. They also did a radon test and the results came back very low. Back on the market at no fault of the seller.
